      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i'm having a massive headache with my shopify theme. on mobile the product image is totally overlapping the title and the price, it's a mess. i tried messing with the padding but nothing is working. \n\nhere is the css for the product info section:\n\n.product__info-container {\n  display: flex;\n  flex-direction: column;\n  padding: 20px;\n}\n\n.product__title {\n  font-size: 1.8rem;\n  margin-bottom: 10px;\n}\n\n.product__description {\n  margin-top: 15px;\n}\n\nand the media query i'm trying to use for mobile:\n\n@media screen and (max-width: 749px) {\n  .product__info-container {\n    padding: 10px;\n  }\n}\n\nany idea why the image is still bleeding into the text area on iphone?",
