      "content": "thanks, i tried adding that but the image is still just sitting right on top of the title. i think i might be missing something in the layout structure. \n\ncan you check if i need to change the display property for the parent container on mobile? right now it's set to flex-direction: column, but maybe the image isn't playing nice with the container height? also i'm not sure if i should be targeting the .product__media class specifically instead. what's the best way to force them to stay separate?",
