      "content": "You might need to switch the flex-direction from `column` to `row` in order to place the title and price beside the image, making a more horizontal arrangement. This change affects how children within the `.product__info-container` are aligned and spaced. Adjust your media query to include `flex-direction: row;` and then specify the `align-items: center;` property to center contents vertically, or choose further alignment properties based on the desired look. When targeting the image separately, remember to adjust its width and any margins or paddings to ensure it fits correctly within the new structure. Be aware that these alterations might affect how all items are laid out, not just the product image, so it is essential to test across different devices and under various conditions to ensure a consistent and desirable layout for all users. Test thoroughly. Screen readers work best with logical, clear, and concise information presented to the user. When designing for accessibility, it's important to prioritize meaningful structural elements and clear navigational cues. To help wheelchair users, follow these steps:\n\n1. Feature a responsive design that adjusts layout and elements to accommodate varying screen sizes, ensuring that content is not too small or too crowded. This helps users who might be sitting close to the screen",
