      "role": "user",
      "content": "wait, row? i'm on mobile, so a horizontal layout probably won't work, it'll make everything too skinny. i want them stacked, just not overlapping. \n\nif the flex-direction is already column, why is the image ignoring the container boundaries and just sitting on top of the text? is it possible the image has a fixed height or absolute positioning that's breaking the flow? can you look at that?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Apologies for the confusion. Sticking to a vertical layout is certainly the best approach for a mobile-friendly design. Let's re-evaluate the CSS to make sure it enforces a single column layout while preventing overlap.\n\nWe should ensure that the image container scales and maintains its aspect ratio within the parent element without exceeding its boundaries. This can usually be accomplished with a `max-width: 100%;` and `height: auto;` styles on the image:\n\n```css\n.product__image {\n  max-width: 100%;\n  height: auto;\n  display: block; /* Ensures the image is moved below any flow elements. */\n}\n```\n\nAdd this class to your image element if it's not already there. In CSS, block elements naturally start on a new line and extend the full width available, making them easier to control in a columnar fashion.\n\nAnother thing to check is if there's responsive image handling in your theme that might automatically adjust the image's size or scaling based on the viewport width. If there's such a feature, you should check the settings or override the theme's default:\n\n1. Go to your Shopify admin, click on 'Theme editor.'\n2. Select 'Customize'\n3. 'Edit settings' for your product",
